13:28.419 --> 13:30.195
That thing is amazing. I mean,

13:30.220 --> 13:31.756
it must be the perfect shape
or something.

13:31.790 --> 13:33.065
It's because it's from church.

13:33.065 --> 13:35.809
This is coated with
the sacred drool of believers.

13:35.834 --> 13:36.971
Huh.

13:36.971 --> 13:39.308
Maybe all this God stuff
isn't a bunch of banana oil.

13:39.341 --> 13:42.144
<i>And that was about as spiritual
as my brother Joey got.</i>

13:42.176 --> 13:43.144
I knew it!

13:43.178 --> 13:45.080
I hope you had your fun!

13:45.112 --> 13:48.000
Because when Father Abdi
gets serious about penance,

13:48.025 --> 13:49.224
you are going to be doing

13:49.224 --> 13:50.560
so many push-ups!

13:56.351 --> 13:58.006
Father, um...

13:58.587 --> 13:59.655
Cecil.

13:59.688 --> 14:00.674
Mike.

14:01.106 --> 14:03.843
I'm glad I caught you
away from the others.

14:03.876 --> 14:06.450
I have questions regarding...

14:06.880 --> 14:08.181
...the wedding night.

14:08.213 --> 14:09.815
Oh, no.

14:09.848 --> 14:11.017
No. I'm not the one to ask.

14:11.050 --> 14:12.985
I can't think of anybody better.

14:13.019 --> 14:16.356
I've always seen you and Peg
as the ideal couple.

14:16.389 --> 14:19.560
The two of you are the reason
I decided to make this move.

14:19.592 --> 14:21.681
- We are?
- Of course.

14:21.681 --> 14:23.615
Seeing the life you made together,

14:23.648 --> 14:25.618
the happiness I missed out on...

14:25.651 --> 14:27.220
What about all the times I came to you

14:27.253 --> 14:28.888
with my nightmare stories?

14:28.921 --> 14:30.657
Like the time Pat
let the possum in the house

14:30.690 --> 14:32.117
and it somehow locked us all out?

14:32.117 --> 14:33.852
It all sounded wonderful.

14:36.754 --> 14:38.267
We need that juiced-up Jesus paddle.

14:38.267 --> 14:39.569
It's great for ping-pong,

14:39.603 --> 14:40.703
and it's the only
credible evidence of God

14:40.737 --> 14:42.072
I have ever seen.

14:42.104 --> 14:43.706
Frank locked it up back at the church.

14:43.739 --> 14:46.403
So we wait till he's asleep,
then take his keys.

14:46.843 --> 14:48.578
You wanna break into the church?

14:48.612 --> 14:49.973
Any court'll tell you

14:49.973 --> 14:51.308
it's not breaking in
if you have the keys.

14:51.340 --> 14:52.522
I don't think that's true.

14:52.522 --> 14:53.890
What happened to my keychain?!

14:56.591 --> 14:58.894
I had them! They were attached to me,

14:58.927 --> 15:00.330
and I to them!

15:00.363 --> 15:02.299
<i>You</i> stole my keys.

15:02.331 --> 15:03.966
What a heinous thing to suggest.

15:03.999 --> 15:06.902
I was totally planning to but
hadn't got around to it yet.

15:06.936 --> 15:08.405
This is a fine howdy-do.

15:08.437 --> 15:09.972
I have no idea where I left them.

15:10.005 --> 15:12.777
So then it's just a matter
of who finds them first.

15:12.777 --> 15:15.343
Timmy, take the kitchen.
Be sure to check the ice box.

15:15.368 --> 15:16.669
Frank spends a lot of time

15:16.669 --> 15:18.203
staring at the Land O'Lakes girl.

15:24.077 --> 15:25.712
Well, we went out of the house,

15:25.745 --> 15:27.647
we were pleasant to people,
we're now done for the year.

15:30.283 --> 15:32.252
I had a talk with Cecil.

15:32.284 --> 15:33.593
I think we really <i> are</i> friends.

15:34.102 --> 15:36.204
Watch out if he asks you
to be his best man.

15:36.237 --> 15:37.806
You don't want to be
standing next to him

15:37.840 --> 15:39.242
holding the ring when
the lightning strikes.

15:39.274 --> 15:41.409
Well, even though he's not
a priest anymore,

15:41.442 --> 15:42.685
I like him.

15:43.479 --> 15:44.901
Why shouldn't he be happy?

15:45.275 --> 15:46.910
Because he broke a commitment, Mike.

15:47.133 --> 15:48.469
Where would the world be if everyone

15:48.502 --> 15:50.238
threw off responsibilities

15:50.271 --> 15:51.606
and skipped through a giggle-forest

15:51.638 --> 15:52.606
chasing happiness?

15:52.640 --> 15:53.909
I know where I'd be.

15:54.138 --> 15:55.039
Nowhere different.

15:55.072 --> 15:56.540
I'd be right here.

15:56.574 --> 15:57.642
That's the thing about

15:57.675 --> 16:00.430
this whole "chasing happiness" nonsense.

16:00.430 --> 16:02.277
I mean, maybe we don't get it

16:02.302 --> 16:04.327
because we've got it.

16:05.214 --> 16:06.449
I'm happy, Peg.

16:06.482 --> 16:07.809
And I think you are, too.

16:07.809 --> 16:09.083
- Shut up.
- I mean it!

16:09.108 --> 16:11.012
This <i> is</i> happiness.

16:11.012 --> 16:13.458
Yeah, well, being happy is exhausting.

16:13.621 --> 16:14.990
Why didn't we pick being wealthy?

16:16.757 --> 16:18.059
Who on Earth?

16:19.761 --> 16:20.566
Cecil?

16:21.382 --> 16:23.051
Loretta broke up with me.

16:23.084 --> 16:25.134
She deep-sixed the wedding.

16:25.644 --> 16:27.844
I need a place to stay.

16:27.869 --> 16:28.883
What happened?

16:28.883 --> 16:30.568
Her daughter took back the blessing.

16:30.568 --> 16:33.176
She says she thinks I killed her father.

16:34.439 --> 16:36.645
Oh, was her daughter at the party?

16:36.670 --> 16:38.805
I would've said hi.

16:41.977 --> 16:43.679
- Thanks, Mike.
- You're welcome.

16:43.711 --> 16:45.380
You'll be okay.

16:47.149 --> 16:49.329
I suppose I could...

16:49.851 --> 16:51.453
let you sleep in my bed.

16:51.486 --> 16:53.455
I think that would be awkward
for me and Peggy.

16:54.766 --> 16:56.669
I'll tell you what would be nice, Mike.

16:57.062 --> 16:58.931
If you would pray with me.

16:58.964 --> 17:00.899
- You want me to...
- If you don't mind.

17:00.933 --> 17:02.367
I've had a rough day.

17:02.367 --> 17:05.337
I always loved the Peace Prayer
of St. Francis.

17:05.368 --> 17:06.371
Okay.

17:09.564 --> 17:11.458
- "Dear Lord..."
- "Dear Lord..."

17:11.458 --> 17:14.128
"...make me an instrument of Thy peace.

17:14.823 --> 17:16.374
Where there is hatred,

17:16.374 --> 17:18.145
let me sow love.

17:18.145 --> 17:19.540
Where there is injury...

17:19.566 --> 17:20.973
- Pardon.
- ...pardon.

17:21.357 --> 17:24.637
Where there is doubt, faith.

17:25.528 --> 17:29.032
Where there is darkness, light.

17:29.066 --> 17:32.620
Where there is sadness, joy."

17:32.620 --> 17:33.822
Headed out.

17:33.854 --> 17:35.089
No using the stove while I'm gone,

17:35.122 --> 17:37.011
unless you make enough for everybody.

17:37.924 --> 17:40.004
- Good morning, boys.
- Good morning.

17:40.029 --> 17:41.770
Mind if I grab a bowl?

17:41.770 --> 17:43.405
We have Count Chocula.

17:43.437 --> 17:45.407
It's not real Count Chocula.

17:45.439 --> 17:48.176
Mom buys Vampire Puffs
and then reuses the box.

17:48.210 --> 17:49.493
I'll take the Trix.

17:49.493 --> 17:50.995
That's just filled with oyster crackers.

17:51.027 --> 17:52.828
- Maybe I'll mix 'em.
- Hm.

17:54.430 --> 17:55.699
Loretta?

17:57.868 --> 17:59.537
Oh, for crying out loud.

17:59.570 --> 18:01.072
Hello, Mrs. Peggy Cleary.

18:01.104 --> 18:03.002
So good to see you. Come in.

18:03.503 --> 18:05.736
You are surprised to find me here.

18:05.761 --> 18:07.495
Not really.

18:07.529 --> 18:09.138
It's starting to seem
like Loretta has a type.

18:09.138 --> 18:11.608
Loretta has been in the bathroom
for quite some time.

18:11.640 --> 18:14.183
Oh. Did you bring her some
of those Somalian doughnuts?

18:14.183 --> 18:15.818
She is crying and heartbroken.

18:15.850 --> 18:18.291
I've come to talk to her
on behalf of Father Dunne.

18:18.316 --> 18:19.905
Please sit.

18:20.251 --> 18:21.720
I'll stand.

18:23.601 --> 18:26.253
She is upset and confused at
something her daughter told her.

18:26.278 --> 18:27.848
Ah, old people.

18:27.848 --> 18:29.416
When are they not upset and confused?

18:29.450 --> 18:31.952
I suggested she ignore
her daughter's concerns.

18:31.985 --> 18:34.755
Too often, parents bend
to their children's wishes.

18:34.789 --> 18:38.260
In my village, if a child
makes demand of the parents,

18:38.292 --> 18:41.029
we put them in a hole and
cover them with fire ants.

18:41.061 --> 18:42.630
That sounds like paradise.

18:42.664 --> 18:43.766
It's wonderful.

18:44.236 --> 18:45.705
Except for all of the ants.

18:45.737 --> 18:47.106
They basically rule our village.

18:47.139 --> 18:49.341
Oh, I'm gonna send your mom
a big can of Raid.

18:49.375 --> 18:51.945
You know, I've been spending
a lot of time

18:51.977 --> 18:54.179
- with your son Frank.
- Oh, sorry about that.

18:54.213 --> 18:55.348
I mean, it's either you or me.

18:55.380 --> 18:56.882
Mm, he has very big ideas

18:56.916 --> 18:58.685
of how our parish should be run.

18:58.717 --> 19:00.954
But he left these keys

19:00.986 --> 19:03.149
- dangling in the rectory door.
- Mm.

19:03.421 --> 19:05.557
I've been watching him
scrambling everywhere

19:05.590 --> 19:07.015
looking desperately to find them.

19:07.436 --> 19:09.104
I could tell him I have the keys,

19:09.137 --> 19:11.574
but instead, I'm letting him suffer.

19:11.608 --> 19:14.310
This will be a good lesson in humility.

19:14.343 --> 19:15.978
Plus it's funny.

19:16.012 --> 19:17.647
Is he sweating a lot?
He gets very sweaty.

19:17.679 --> 19:19.483
He's sweating a lot, yes.

19:19.515 --> 19:21.035
Here. You take these.

19:21.132 --> 19:22.668
Now you get to decide for how long

19:22.701 --> 19:25.013
Frank feels miserable.

19:25.213 --> 19:26.848
- What a thoughtful gift.
- Hm.

19:26.882 --> 19:28.683
Oh, Father.

19:29.253 --> 19:31.407
I feel like our family
might have gotten off

19:31.407 --> 19:32.738
on the wrong foot with you.

19:33.401 --> 19:35.761
Mike can be a little racist.

19:36.205 --> 19:37.440
We'll work on it,

19:38.220 --> 19:39.955
try not to be so small-minded.

19:39.980 --> 19:41.949
That would be a very good goal

19:41.982 --> 19:44.733
for all of us, Mrs. Peggy Cleary.

19:44.733 --> 19:45.934
Okay, enough, Loretta!

19:45.968 --> 19:47.232
You're making a meal of this!

19:52.232 --> 19:53.967
I used to be better at ping-pong.

19:54.000 --> 19:55.936
Or everyone was letting you win.

19:55.970 --> 19:57.704
Life's gonna be different
without that collar.

19:57.738 --> 19:59.025
You're telling me.

19:59.025 --> 20:00.994
Lately, I've been getting
the finger in traffic.

20:01.028 --> 20:03.198
Well, the good news is,
now you can give it back.

20:03.231 --> 20:04.566
Oh, I have.

20:04.599 --> 20:06.701
Hello, Cecil.

20:06.734 --> 20:09.003
- Loretta!
- Oh,

20:09.035 --> 20:11.739
I'm so sorry about our misunderstanding.

20:11.773 --> 20:13.727
Father Abdi and I set her straight.

20:14.166 --> 20:15.635
You and Father Abdi?

20:15.667 --> 20:18.404
You're the only one allowed
to have a priest friend?

20:18.436 --> 20:20.572
I'm just gonna
stop listening to Sabrina.

20:20.606 --> 20:22.608
I'm not even sure Earl was her father.

20:22.640 --> 20:24.776
If Catholicism has taught me anything,

20:24.810 --> 20:28.313
it's that stuff that
happened a long time ago

20:28.483 --> 20:30.252
doesn't really matter at all.

20:30.284 --> 20:31.253
Oh.

20:31.285 --> 20:32.186
Take it next door.

20:32.219 --> 20:33.588
And close the drapes.

20:35.779 --> 20:37.582
Look how happy they are.

20:37.615 --> 20:39.099
Why wouldn't they be?

20:39.099 --> 20:40.368
They got a long dirt nap

20:40.400 --> 20:42.170
waiting for 'em right over the horizon.

20:42.570 --> 20:44.906
We still got to slog through 20,
30 years.

20:46.329 --> 20:48.398
You still won't admit that we're happy?

20:48.432 --> 20:50.818
Happiness comes in
the afterlife, which is why

20:50.843 --> 20:52.314
we <i> don't want</i> to outlive our kids.

20:52.339 --> 20:53.290
Oh, God, no.

20:53.290 --> 20:55.426
Imagine getting to Heaven
and <i> they're</i> waiting for us.

20:55.460 --> 20:56.729
That's what's great

20:56.761 --> 20:58.896
about the way we raised these animals.

20:58.930 --> 21:01.376
What are the chances we see
all eight of them up there?

21:01.376 --> 21:02.644
I like our odds.

